  <data key="d5">1777418926</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Commission">
  <data key="d0">European Commission</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Commission is the executive branch of the European Union, led by Ursula von der Leyen, responsible for proposing legislation and implementing policies.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Commission is the executive branch of the European Union, led by Ursula von der Leyen, and is subject to dismissal via a successful motion of censure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ffb76e13354613b80f653af13be1e243&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9537adb639f6d92a3c655a2e0dc6a434</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\20.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\21.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777418926</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European People's Party">
  <data key="d0">European People's Party</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European People's Party is a center-right political party in the European Union, of which Ursula von der Leyen is a representative.&lt;SEP&gt;The European People's Party is a centrist political group in the European Parliament that consistently votes against motions of censure against the Commission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ffb76e13354613b80f653af13be1e243&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9537adb639f6d92a3c655a2e0dc6a434</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\20.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\21.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777418926</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Far-Right Fractures">
  <data key="d0">Far-Right Fractures</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Far-Right Fractures refer to political groups in the European Parliament, such as "Patriots for Europe," that oppose von der Leyen's policies on migration, sovereignty, and culture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ffb76e13354613b80f653af13be1e243</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\20.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777418278</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Far-Left Fractures">
  <data key="d0">Far-Left Fractures</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Far-Left Fractures refer to political groups in the European Parliament, such as "The Left," that criticize von der Leyen for neoliberalism, militarization, and corporate favoritism.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ffb76e13354613b80f653af13be1e243</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\20.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777418278</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Patriots for Europe">
  <data key="d0">Patriots for Europe</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Patriots for Europe is a far-right political faction in the European Parliament that opposes von der Leyen’s policies on migration, national sovereignty, and cultural progressivism.&lt;SEP&gt;Patriots for Europe (PfE) is an ultraright political group in the European Parliament that initiated two motions of censure in October 2025 and January 2026.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ffb76e13354613b80f653af13be1e243&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9537adb639f6d92a3c655a2e0dc6a434</data>
