</node>
<node id="Militant Accelerationism">
  <data key="d0">Militant Accelerationism</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Militant accelerationism is the core ideology of Atomwaffen Division and Terrorgram-сцена, advocating the deliberate destabilization and collapse of democratic societies through violence, terror, and chaos, inspired by Charles Manson’s "Helter Skelter" interpretation.&lt;SEP&gt;Militant Accelerationism is a neo-Nazi magazine that incorporates pop culture and gaming motifs to promote radicalization, including references to "Game of Thrones."</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4117a24ac776e64ee5b10c9c825a2778&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9a14fc1e13b7bdf9ed3cf57cf0801e3</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\22.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\24.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777419681</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="White Sharia">
  <data key="d0">White Sharia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">White Sharia is an ideological construct adopted by Atomwaffen Division and Terrorgram-сцена, mimicking Islamic sharia law as a framework for white supremacist governance and moral codes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4117a24ac776e64ee5b10c9c825a2778</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\22.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777419334</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="White Jihad">
  <data key="d0">White Jihad</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">White Jihad is an ideological concept promoted by Atomwaffen Division and Terrorgram-сцена, adapting jihadist terminology and martyrdom culture to white supremacist extremism.&lt;SEP&gt;White jihad refers to the phenomenon where white supremacist neo-Nazis adopt jihadist rhetoric, symbolism, and tactics, framing their violence as a religiously legitimized struggle.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4117a24ac776e64ee5b10c9c825a2778&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4698e80f89aaeb2bfe1d0d03eef662a4</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\22.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\23.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777419918</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Saints">
  <data key="d0">Saints</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Saints refers to the glorification of lone-actor terrorists and shooters within Atomwaffen Division and Terrorgram-сцена, mirroring the jihadist cult of martyrdom.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4117a24ac776e64ee5b10c9c825a2778</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\22.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777419334</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lone Actor Strategy">
  <data key="d0">Lone Actor Strategy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Lone Actor Strategy is a tactic adopted by Atomwaffen Division and Terrorgram-сцена, inspired by ISIS, emphasizing decentralized, individual attacks radicalized through online networks without direct command structure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4117a24ac776e64ee5b10c9c825a2778</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\22.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777419334</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2025 SAFE Report">
  <data key="d0">2025 SAFE Report</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2025 SAFE Report is a document published by the antiterrorism center of Baden-Württemberg (SAT BW), confirming the convergence of neo-Nazi and jihadist extremist ideologies in Germany.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4117a24ac776e64ee5b10c9c825a2778</data>
