  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cumulative extremism is a British criminological term used to describe the mutual radicalization between opposing extremist groups, including white supremacists and jihadists.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4698e80f89aaeb2bfe1d0d03eef662a4</data>
